### Weather Tool Integration Examples

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7029
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Create a new conversation session
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/session
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

### 2. Ask about weather (tool will be automatically called)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What is the weather in New York?",
  "sessionId": "YOUR_SESSION_ID_HERE"
}

### 3. Follow-up question using weather context
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "Should I wear a jacket today?",
  "sessionId": "YOUR_SESSION_ID_HERE"
}

### 4. Weather in different format
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "How's the temperature in London?",
  "sessionId": "YOUR_SESSION_ID_HERE"
}

### 5. Weather comparison
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What's the weather like in Paris compared to what we discussed earlier?",
  "sessionId": "YOUR_SESSION_ID_HERE"
}

### 6. Regular conversation (no tools)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "Tell me a joke",
  "sessionId": "YOUR_SESSION_ID_HERE"
}

### 7. Weather with calculation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/chat
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "message": "What's the weather in Tokyo and convert the temperature to Fahrenheit?",
  "sessionId": "YOUR_SESSION_ID_HERE"
}

### 8. Get conversation history (will show tool usage)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/session/YOUR_SESSION_ID_HERE/history
